{
  "text": "That's okay. I don't think that was a good question anyway. And Ra initially planned for helping the Egyptians with their evolution. What was the most or the primary concept, and also secondary and tertiary, if you can name those, that Ra wished to impart to the Egyptians. In other words, what was Ra's training plan or schedule for making the Egyptians aware of what was necessary for the revolution. We wished to impress upon those who wished to learn of unity that in a unity all paradoxes are resolved. All that is broken is healed. All that is forgotten is brought to light. In that our intention when we walked among your peoples was to manifest that which was requested by those learned teachers to which we had come. But already in the opening of blue and indigo up through this point, the archetypes function as the great basis or plinth of a builded structure or statue, keeping the mind complex, viable, level, and available as a resource whenever it may be evoked. This is the point at which a clear and conscious consideration of the archetypical mind is useful.",
